For Validating JSON Files
Install JSON Processor (jq)


sudo apt-get install jq
Validate JSON File
Replace test.json with the name of your JSON file:

bash
Copy code
jq . test.json
Command Explanation:
jq: A command-line JSON processor.
.: Outputs the entire JSON file in a pretty-printed format.
If the JSON is invalid, you'll see an error message indicating the problem.